An '''air pollution episode''' is an unusual combination of emissions and [[meteorology]] that gives rise to high levels of air pollution over a large area. Examples of air pollution episodes include: *[[1930 Meuse Valley fog|1930 Meuse Valley]] Episode *[[1939 St. Louis smog|1939 Saint Louis]] Episode<ref>http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/a-look-back-black-tuesday-spurred-crackdown-on-coal-pollution/article_00c3b6cd-ba69-5a19-b498-fbc29f9630c4.html</ref> * [[1948 Donora smog|1948 Donora]] Episode<ref>https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=103359330</ref> * [[Great Smog|1952 London]] Episode<ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-london-20615186</ref> * [[1997 Indonesian forest fires]] Episode<ref>http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2013/06/25/a-nation-fire-what-should-we-learn-19971998-haze.html</ref> * [[2005 Malaysian Haze]] Episode<ref>http://www.ijens.org/Vol_13_I_02/113905-1302-7272-IJBAS-IJENS.pdf</ref> * [[2006 Southeast Asian Haze]] Episode * [[Bhopal disaster|1984 Bhopal Gas Tragedy]] Episode
