The '''Ice Sheet Mass Balance Inter-comparison Exercise''' (IMBIE) is an international scientific collaboration attempting to improve estimates of the amounts of ice contained in ice sheets around the world and of their contribution to [[sea level rise]] and to publish data and analyses concerning these subjects. IMBIE was founded in 2011 and is a collaboration between the [[European Space Agency]] (ESA) and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration ([[NASA]]) of the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imbie.org/about-the-project/ |title=About IMBIE |publisher=Ice Sheet Mass Balance Inter-comparison Exercise (IMBIE) | accessdate=2018-06-14}}</ref>

