{{Infobox scientist |name = Jacques Huber |image = Jacques Huber00.gif |image_size = |caption = <center>Jacques Huber |birth_date = 13 October 1867 |birth_place = |death_date = 18 February 1914 (aged 66) |death_place = [[Belém]], [[Pará]], [[Brazil]] |residence = |citizenship = [[Switzerland|Swiss]] and [[Brazil]]ian |nationality = Swiss-German |ethnicity = |fields = [[Botany]] |workplaces = [[Museu Paraense Emílio Goeldi]] |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |academic_advisors = |doctoral_students = |notable_students = |known_for = |author_abbrev_bot = Huber |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = [[Adolpho Ducke]] |awards = |religion = |signature = <!--(filename only)--> |footnotes = Director of Museu Paraense Emílio Goeldi (1907-1914) }}
'''Jacques Huber''' (13 October 1867 [[Schleitheim]] – 18 February 1914 [[Belém]]) was a [[Swiss]]-[[Brazil]]ian [[botanist]] who did pioneering work on the flora of the [[Amazon Rainforest|Amazon]] from 1895 until his death. He created and organized the herbarium and arboretum in [[Belém]], Brazil, and was director of the [[Museu Paraense Emílio Goeldi]] from 1907 until he died.
==Works== *[http://mertzdigital.nybg.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/p9016coll23/id/14135/rec/37 ''Materiaes para a flora amazonica''] (Vol. 1) *[http://mertzdigital.nybg.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/p9016coll23/id/14156/rec/38 ''Materiaes para a flora amazonica''] (Vol.2) *[http://mertzdigital.nybg.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/p9016coll23/id/14211/rec/39 ''Materiaes para a flora amazonica''] (Vol.5) *[http://mertzdigital.nybg.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/p9016coll23/id/14336/rec/40 ''Materiaes para a flora amazonica''] (Vol.6) *[http://mertzdigital.nybg.org/cdm/compoundobject/collection/p9016coll23/id/14484/rec/41 ''Materiaes para a flora amazonica''] (Vol.7)
